column1: #Text=Are you preparing for a big overnight festival ?
#Text=Packing wisely can help you have a great time !
#Text=Choose a Suitcase that will fit your clothes .
#Text=Depending on how long you stay , depend on how big your Suitcase should be .
#Text=Choose a Suitcase that is sturdy , and is weather resistant .
#Text=When going to a outdoor music festival , it can rain , and storm , so you want to make sure your Suitcase can keep your clothes dry , and one that wo n’t fall apart if it gets wet .
#Text=Use a Suitcase that you can easily carry , or pull .
#Text=You do n’t want your bag to be so big that you have a hard time traveling with it .
#Text=Research what the weather will be like the days you go .
#Text=Below , under Clothes , are some suggestions on what to take .
#Text=Make sure you pick your clothes to match the weather .
#Text=Make a plan of what you want to wear when .
#Text=Fold your clothes , so they will fit in your Suitcase .

#Text=Using your clothes plan , pack in chronological ( E. g , If you are going to the festival on Monday , and will be staying until Friday , pack the clothes you will wear on Friday on the bottom of your bag , and the clothes for Monday , on the top .
#Text=That way , they will be in order ) .
#Text=This is the first thing you will do when you arrive at your destination .
#Text=Remember to put a tarp down under , and over your tent .
#Text=If you are staying in a RV , or motor home , you will need to get that all set up , and leveled .
#Text=Any clothes you have out of your bag , make sure to put them all back in .
#Text=Check everywhere you have been to make sure you have everything , and are n’t leaving anything behind .
#Text=Take down your tent , and pack it up .
#Text=You want to leave your camp site the same way it was when you first arrived .
#Text=Even though the festival will have vendors for food , it is good to bring your own food so you do n’t have to spend money every time you want something to eat , or drink .
#Text=You will want to pack all of this food in a cooler .
#Text=Either separate ones , or one big one .
#Text=You will need ice packs , and ice , to keep the food cold , and from spoiling .
#Text=For hot weather you will want to bring clothes that are made to worn in the summer , but you also want to be prepared for cool weather .
#Text=If you are going for 7 days , pack for 11 days .
#Text=Or , just to be prepared , pack for 14 days .
#Text=Bring moisture wicking clothes , or natural fabrics .
#Text=This is n’t a natural fabric , but it is good to wear in hot weather .
#Text=Pajamas ( it could get cold at night , so bring long sleep wear , as well as light weight ones )
#Text=Sweatpants or yoga pants ( light weight , and or heavy )
#Text=Sweat shirts ( light weight , and or heavy )
#Text=Toilet paper ( always a good thing to have , encase of an emergency )
#Text=Hair products ( Hair spray , leave in conditioner , ETC )
#Text=This is a list of objects you can use at your camp site , as well as for on the car ride down , so you have something to do when not participating in the festival .
#Text=2 tarps , for under and over your tent .
#Text=So rain , and morning dew does n’t get in .
#Text=Food ( See , “ Food to Take . ” ) and drinks
#Text=Sandwiches ( Subs , peanut butter and jelly sandwiches , deli meat sandwiches , ETC )
#Text=Just Add Water Pancakes ( for if you have a grill )
#Text=Eggs ( for if you have a grill )
#Text=You can bring re-usable water bottles so you can re-fill it .
#Text=Any sports drink ( Such as , Gatorade , Body Armor , and Red Bull )
#Text=Coffee ( You will need a french coffee maker )
#Text=If you have one , bring a little propane grill .
#Text=You can put your first aid contents together in any plastic container .
#Text=Gauze pads , and roller gauze in assorted sizes
#Text=Plastic bags to act as a trash can
#Text=Sterile eyewash , such as a saline solution
#Text=Activated charcoal ( use only if instructed by your poison control center )
#Text=Aspirin and non-aspirin pain relievers ( never give aspirin to children )
